<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="402" pageId="5" pageNumber="401" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1890,2023]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,896]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="402" pageId="5" pageNumber="401">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1890,1915]" pageId="5" pageNumber="401">Description.</emphasis>
See 
<tableCitation box="[403,499,1890,1915]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetBox="[159,1343,308,1270]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphometric data of for BarIlIus ardens (n = 6, ZSI / SRC, F. 8812, F. 8813, MKC 385), B. canarensIs (n = 3, ZSI / SRC, F. 8814, MKC 415), B. malabarIcus (n = 10, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, F. 8816, MKC 416), B. bakerI (n = 6, MKC 295, 384)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFF48FF16FF2E" pageId="5" pageNumber="401" tableUuid="DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFF48FF16FF2E">
Tables 
<number box="[485,499,1890,1914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="401" value="1.0">1</number>
</tableCitation>
and 
<number box="[558,572,1890,1914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="401" value="2.0">
<tableCitation box="[558,572,1890,1914]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,239,1338,1361]" captionTargetBox="[159,1314,1421,1856]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 2. Meristic data of BarIlIus ardens (n = 6, ZSI / SRC, F. 8812, F. 8813, MKC 385), B. canarensIs (n = 3, ZSI / SRC, F. 8814, MKC 415), B. malabarIcus (n = 10, ZSI / SRC, F. 8815, F. 8816, MKC 416), B. bakerI (n = 6, MKC 295, 384)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFAEAFA83FAB0" pageId="5" pageNumber="401" tableUuid="DF2D6636CD75FFC36DACFAEAFA83FAB0">2</tableCitation>
</number>
for morphometric and meristic characters, and 
<figureCitation box="[1121,1229,1890,1915]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1829,1851]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,805,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,805,1807]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Barilius canarensis, MKC 415, A, 83.7 mm SL; B, 81.9 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242896/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="401">
Figures 
<number box="[1215,1229,1890,1914]" pageId="5" pageNumber="401" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[1288,1302,1890,1915]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1565,1587]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,951,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[217,1369,951,1542]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Barilius canarensis, ZSI / SRC, F. 8814, 81.9 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242897/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="401">
<number box="[1288,1302,1890,1915]" pageId="5" pageNumber="401" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
for general appearance. Body deep, its depth about one-third SL, laterally compressed, dorsal profile slightly curved, ventral profile deeply convex. Caudal peduncle deep, depth almost equal to length. Head small, length about one-fourth SL, depth more than three-fourths length, dorsal profile almost straight, a slightly raised at nape. Eyes large, placed forward, their diameter about one-third HL. Mouth oblique, angle of gape almost reaching posterior margin of orbit. Two pairs of minute barbels (rostral and maxillary). Nostrils closer to eye than to snout tip. Lower jaw slightly longer than upper jaw. Snout length about one-third HL.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">
Dorsal fin with 
<number box="[376,390,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
simple and 
<number box="[526,553,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="10.0">10</number>
½ (
<number box="[592,606,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
) branched rays, posterior margin slightly concave, origin anterior to analfin origin. Pelvic fin short, not reaching anal-fin origin, with 
<number box="[859,873,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
simple and 
<number box="[1017,1031,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number box="[1050,1064,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
) branched rays. Anal-fin with 
<number box="[1422,1436,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
simple and 
<number box="[283,310,332,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="13.0">13</number>
½ (
<number box="[350,364,332,356]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
) branched rays, ventral margin deeply concave, a sharp curve among first few branched rays. Pectoral fin with 
<number box="[348,362,368,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
simple and 
<number box="[503,531,368,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="10.0">10</number>
(
<number box="[548,558,368,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
)– 
<number box="[585,613,368,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="11.0">11</number>
(
<number box="[630,645,368,392]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.0">2</number>
) branched rays. Caudal fin deeply forked, lobes subequal, lower lobe slightly longer, with 
<number box="[388,398,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[416,431,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="9.0">9</number>
+ 
<number box="[449,463,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="8.0">8</number>
+ 
<number box="[481,491,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
principal rays. Lateral line complete, slightly curved, with 
<number box="[1169,1197,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="35.0">35</number>
(
<number box="[1214,1229,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.0">2</number>
) or 
<number box="[1279,1307,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="36.0">36</number>
(
<number box="[1326,1338,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
) + 
<number box="[1381,1395,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
(
<number box="[1413,1427,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
) pored scales. Predorsal scales 
<number box="[488,518,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="14.0">14</number>
(
<number box="[527,537,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
)– 
<number box="[562,590,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="15.0">15</number>
(
<number box="[607,623,440,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.0">2</number>
); scales in transverse line on body ½ 
<number box="[1036,1049,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="8.0">8</number>
/ 
<number box="[1059,1068,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1078,1093,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.0">2</number>
(
<number box="[1107,1121,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.0">2</number>
)– 
<number box="[1145,1159,439,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.0">2</number>
½ (
<number box="[1198,1210,440,464]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
) between dorsal-fin origin and pelvic-fin base, 
<number box="[457,471,476,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.0">2</number>
½ (
<number box="[510,524,476,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
) scales between lateral line and anal-fin base. Gill rakers, slender, well-defined, with 
<number box="[208,222,512,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
(
<number box="[238,252,512,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
) + 
<number box="[291,305,512,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number box="[321,337,512,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.0">2</number>
), 
<number box="[359,373,512,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number box="[390,402,512,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.0">1</number>
) rakers on the first gill arch. Fifth ceratobranchial with 
<number box="[1027,1040,511,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="5.0">5</number>
+ 
<number box="[1056,1071,511,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1087,1101,511,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.0">2</number>
teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1244,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1453,1475]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,193,1431]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[217,1369,193,1432]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Fifth ceratobranchial of, A, Barilius ardens, MKC 385, 85.5 mm SL; B, B. canarensis, MKC 415, 83.7 mm SL; C, B. bakeri, MKC 384, 68.7 mm SL (Scale bar = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242895/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">
Fig. 
<number box="[1230,1244,512,536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,548,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Coloration.</emphasis>
In life (see 
<figureCitation box="[471,539,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1829,1851]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,805,1807]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[217,1369,805,1807]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Barilius canarensis, MKC 415, A, 83.7 mm SL; B, 81.9 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242896/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">
Fig. 
<number box="[523,539,548,572]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
), body bright greenish silver, with two rows of spots along flank, first row with 
<number box="[151,204,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="10.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="9.0">9–11</number>
oval bluish-green spots 
<number box="[472,514,584,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
scales high, 
<number box="[654,693,583,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2</number>
scales wide and second row with 
<number box="[1074,1115,584,608]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
smaller spots reaching up to anal-fin origin. Sometimes in large specimens spots of second row further breaking up into a smaller third row consisting of 
<number box="[302,344,656,680]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
minute spots. Dorsal fin and anal fin bases black, fin margins lined with white. Pelvic fins tipped white; pectoral fins tipped orange. Caudal fin black, tips white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">
Preserved specimens (
<figureCitation box="[458,530,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1565,1587]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,951,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[217,1369,951,1542]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Barilius canarensis, ZSI / SRC, F. 8814, 81.9 mm SL." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242897/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">
Fig. 
<number box="[516,530,727,752]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) lose bright colours: greyish brown, darker on dorsum, progressively lighter towards abdomen, which is white. Spots on body dark grey. Fins opaque; dorsal, anal and caudal with black bases.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="402" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,799,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[363,584,800,824]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Barilius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="6" pageNumber="402" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canarensis">
<emphasis box="[363,584,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="402">Barilius canarensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from the Netravathi River in south Canara (south-western Karnataka) during our surveys, but probably occurs through a wider range in the south Karnataka and north Kerala regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
